name: 10-25976-iavb-rl59
notes: Through the ACP Grant, NSWA commissioned TetraTech to complete the repeatable Sturgeon River Water Quality Monitoring Program along the main stem and tributaries from 2021 - 2022. Four sampling events were conducted, one in spring (April/May) and another in summer (August/September) of each of 2021 and 2022. The purpose of the program is to extend the baseline database and identify issues and eventually be able to detect trends in water quality over time.

notes_translated.en: Through the ACP Grant, NSWA commissioned TetraTech to complete the repeatable Sturgeon River Water Quality Monitoring Program along the main stem and tributaries from 2021 - 2022. Four sampling events were conducted, one in spring (April/May) and another in summer (August/September) of each of 2021 and 2022. The purpose of the program is to extend the baseline database and identify issues and eventually be able to detect trends in water quality over time.
notes_translated.fr: Grâce à la subvention ACP, la NSWA a chargé TetraTech de mener à bien le programme reproductible de surveillance de la qualité de l'eau de la rivière Sturgeon le long du cours principal et de ses affluents de 2021 à 2022. Quatre échantillonnages ont été effectués, l'un au printemps (avril/mai) et l'autre en été (août/septembre) en 2021 et 2022. Le but du programme est d'étendre la base de données de référence et d'identifier les problèmes et, à terme, de pouvoir détecter les tendances de la qualité de l'eau au fil du temps.
